President Obama announced his intent to nominate Peggy E. Gustafson as Inspector General of the Small Business Administration and George H. Cohen as Director of the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service. Peggy Gustafson currently serves as General Counsel to Senator Claire McCaskill and has experience in government oversight issues. George Cohen has had a long career as a labor lawyer, negotiator, and mediator. He has been a partner at a law firm and has served as an appellate court attorney with the National Labor Relations Board. In the past three years, he has worked as a mediator and has successfully mediated numerous complex disputes.